# =====================================================================
# Si-Chip .gitignore
# Adapted from the canonical DevolaFlow ignore policy (v8.3.0 Q-5).
# =====================================================================

# --- Python --------------------------------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.egg
*.egg-info/
.eggs/
dist/
build/
.venv/
venv/
env/

# --- Testing / coverage -------------------------------------------------
.pytest_cache/
.tox/
htmlcov/
.coverage
.coverage.*
coverage.xml
coverage.json
*.cover

# --- Type checkers / linters -------------------------------------------
.ruff_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.pyre/
.pytype/

# --- Node (for any frontend / demo / docs) ------------------------------
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*

# --- Editor / IDE -------------------------------------------------------
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
*.iml

# --- OS noise -----------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
Desktop.ini

# --- Secrets / env ------------------------------------------------------
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
*.pem
*.key

# --- Logs ---------------------------------------------------------------
*.log

# --- DevolaFlow runtime state (created at execution time) --------------
.workflow-state/
.workflow/

# --- GitHub Pages / Jekyll build outputs ----------------------------------
docs/_site/
docs/.jekyll-cache/
docs/.jekyll-metadata

# --- Lockfiles for tools we do NOT vendor (kept out of v0 release) -------
poetry.lock
uv.lock
Pipfile.lock

# =====================================================================
# DevolaFlow `.local/` workspace policy (v8.3.0 Q-5, resolved 2026-04-22)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# The `.local/` tree carries TWO sub-trees that MUST be tracked in git:
#   (a) the full `.local/.agent/` workspace
#   (b) `.local/memory/specs/` source-of-truth specs
# The rest of `.local/` (feedbacks, tasks, index, MEMORY.md, learnings)
# remains gitignored as runtime/agent state.
#
# Strategy: ignore the *contents* of `.local/` (not the directory itself),
# so Git recurses into it; then re-include the public sub-trees; then
# re-ignore secrets and runtime state inside those sub-trees as defense
# in depth. (A bare `.local/` ignore would block re-include patterns per
# gitignore docs.)
# =====================================================================
.local/*
# Re-include the agent workspace tree:
!.local/.agent/
!.local/.agent/**
# Re-include source-of-truth specs without re-including the rest of memory:
!.local/memory/
.local/memory/*
!.local/memory/specs/
!.local/memory/specs/**
# Re-include the canonical research evidence library (frozen for v0.1.0):
!.local/research/
!.local/research/**

# Re-include dogfood evidence (per spec §10 persistence contract):
!.local/dogfood/
!.local/dogfood/**
# Defense in depth — re-ignore secrets / runtime state / per-change learnings
# even after the un-ignore patterns above:
.local/.agent/active/*/learnings.jsonl
.local/.agent/archive/*/learnings.jsonl
.local/memory/operational.jsonl
.local/memory/session_state.json
.local/memory/prefs.md
.local/memory/plugin_install.log
